SPU GCC: -mspurs-job / -mspurs-job-initialize / -mspurs-task driver flags

Adds three driver flags that propagate through to the linker so the
final SPU ELF carries the e_flags value the SPRX dispatcher uses to
identify the program type.

    -mspurs-job             -> ld --spurs-job             (e_flags = 1)
    -mspurs-job-initialize  -> ld --spurs-job-initialize  (e_flags = 2)
    -mspurs-task            -> ld --spurs-task            (e_flags = 3)

Pairs with the binutils patch
patches/spu/binutils-2.42/0001-spu-elf-spurs-job-flags.patch which
implements the corresponding linker options.

Spec semantics match the documented ABI in
docs/abi/spurs-job-entry-point.md.  Stock SPU GCC + binutils emits
e_flags=0 which the jobbin2 packaging path treats as "unspecified".

gcc/config/spu/spu.opt   - three new -m driver flags
gcc/config/spu/spu-elf.h - extend LINK_SPEC to forward the flags

--- a/gcc/config/spu/spu.opt
+++ b/gcc/config/spu/spu.opt
@@ -47,6 +47,18 @@
 Target Report Mask(STD_MAIN)
 Use standard main function as entry for startup.
 
+mspurs-job
+Target Report RejectNegative
+Build as a SPURS Job 2.0 binary (without job CRT). Sets ELF e_flags=1.
+
+mspurs-job-initialize
+Target Report RejectNegative
+Build as a SPURS Job 2.0 binary with job CRT. Sets ELF e_flags=2.
+
+mspurs-task
+Target Report RejectNegative
+Build as a SPURS Task binary. Sets ELF e_flags=3.
+
 mbranch-hints
 Target Report Mask(BRANCH_HINTS)
 Generate branch hints for branches.
--- a/gcc/config/spu/spu-elf.h
+++ b/gcc/config/spu/spu-elf.h
@@ -63,7 +63,11 @@
 
 #define EH_FRAME_THROUGH_COLLECT2 1
 
-#define LINK_SPEC "%{mlarge-mem: --defsym __stack=0xfffffff0 }"
+#define LINK_SPEC "%{mlarge-mem: --defsym __stack=0xfffffff0 }\
+ %{mspurs-job: --spurs-job}\
+ %{mspurs-job-initialize: --spurs-job-initialize}\
+ %{mspurs-task: --spurs-task}\
+"
 
 #define LIB_SPEC "-( %{!shared:%{g*:-lg}} -lc -lgloss -) \
     %{mno-atomic-updates:-lgcc_cachemgr_nonatomic; :-lgcc_cachemgr} \
